3. Post-Class Assignment (Project) (1 hour)

Project: Build a To-Do List with Persistent Storage:

Create a to-do list app that allows adding, deleting, and displaying tasks

Store tasks persistently in Local Storage as an array of objects (each task with text and status)

On page load, retrieve and display tasks from Local Storage

Use Session Storage to save temporary form input data while the user is typing (simulate session persistence)

Allow marking tasks as complete and update storage accordingly

Deliverable:

Submit.html and.js files with comments explaining storage use

Include screenshots or a short video showing persistent behavior